<!--
Synthetic NEMSIS v3.5 PatientCareReport — realistic-shape polytrauma export.

This fixture is the size and section-richness of an actual ePCR that an
EMS unit would generate at the end of a transport: full Header,
eDispatch/eResponse/eScene boilerplate, multi-point eVitals progression,
medical history, allergies, on-scene medications, procedures, narrative,
disposition. None of the patient-identifying values are real.

Profile: 38-year-old male, restrained driver in a high-energy MVC,
arrival at receiving Level I trauma center. Hypotensive and
deteriorating en route — initial GCS 13 → 8 over 7 minutes,
SBP 102 → 78. Polytrauma with presumed TBI, intracranial hemorrhage,
hemorrhagic shock, and unstable spine.

What this exercises that the persona-001..008 fixtures don't:
- Multi-section NEMSIS noise (eDispatch, eResponse, eScene, eOther,
  eMedications, eProcedures, eExam, eNarrative, eDisposition,
  eTimes) that the adapter must ignore cleanly
- Multi-group eVitals progression where only the LATEST group should
  drive the Patient (deterioration must surface, not initial values)
- eHistory.06 medication list carrying non-anticoagulants (acetaminophen
  PRN, lisinopril) — must NOT trip the anticoagulant heuristic
- Realistic ICD-10 cause-of-injury (V44.5XXA, "driver of pickup truck or
  van injured in collision with car") rather than a stub V code
-->
